oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Real photo of Pvt. Thomas Cleve Maness
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Pvt. Thomas Cleve Maness, Btry. B, 318th FA, a farmer from Beech Bluff, Tennessee, posed for this studio photograph in what appears to be a M1910 summer uniform coat with woolen breeches, M1912 leggings and a campaign hat. The backdrop is decorated with images of a cannon and a stack of arms with United States flag behind and to the proper left of the subject. Cleves served from August 1918 until June1919.
